    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to evaluate the sensitivity of pump-induced hemolysis to variations in component dimensions for a centrifugal blood pump used during cardiopulmonary bypass surgery. Model influence is MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect tolerance decision could impact clinical hemolysis levels). Model Risk Level 2.",
    "deviceClass": "Class II",
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou1-cpb",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to identify worst-case operating conditions for hemolysis across 5 flow-speed combinations for a Class II CPB device. Results compared against predicate device hemolysis using relative hemolysis index (RH < 1 acceptance criterion).",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "name": "COU1: Cardiopulmonary bypass use (Class II)",
    "type": "ContextOfUse"
  },
  "hasValidationResult": [
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/rh-index-primary",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Primary relative hemolysis index validation against FDA pump experimental data",
      "description": "This validation result captures the comparison of CFD-predicted relative hemolysis index (RH) against the experimental dataset collected by Morrison et al. (2019) across all five flow-speed operating points (2 L/min at 2500 RPM, 3 L/min at 2500 RPM, 4 L/min at 2500 RPM, 3 L/min at 3500 RPM, and 5 L/min at 3500 RPM). The CFD simulation employed a power-law hemolysis damage accumulation model integrated along Lagrangian particle trajectories seeded at the pump inlet. Mesh independence was confirmed at 4.2 million polyhedral cells (GCI < 2.1% for all operating points). Turbulence was modelled using the SST k-omega closure. Boundary conditions were derived from the experimental test loop: inlet flow rates measured by Coriolis flowmeter (±0.5%), rotational speed controlled by closed-loop servo to ±5 RPM. The predicted RH values ranged from 0.61 to 0.94 across operating points, all satisfying the RH < 1 acceptance criterion. Mean absolute percentage error relative to experimental MIH measurements was 8.3%, within the 15% tolerance band established in the credibility plan. The simulation campaign was executed on the university HPC cluster between 14 March 2023 and 02 April 2023 using ANSYS Fluent 2022 R2, with results post-processed in Python 3.10 using an in-house hemolysis integration script (version 2.4.1, SHA-256 verified). All raw result files are archived in the institutional repository under accession MOR-2023-CFD-001. The detailed narrative above documents the generation process; the credibility assessment team considered this prose record sufficient to establish traceability of the result.",
      "comparedAgainst": "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/fda-pump-experimental-hemolysis"
    },
