      "name": "Mesh independence and discretization error quantification",
      "description": "Grid convergence index study performed on three systematically refined meshes (1.1M, 4.2M, and 14.8M cells). GCI for predicted hydraulic head at the design point was 1.8%; GCI for volume-averaged shear stress magnitude was 2.1%. Richardson extrapolation confirmed monotonic convergence. Discretization error is bounded and acceptable for MRL 2.",
      "comparedAgainst": "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/cfd-mesh-study-results",
      "prov:wasGeneratedBy": "https://uofa.net/morrison/activity/gci-study-2023-02"
